Orchestrates leaf-first, then rollup summarization of a source tree via pluggable filesystem and LLM agent. Loads two prompt templates once, generates `.ctx` files for each target source file, then walks affected directories leaf-up (deepest first) to generate rollups that compose the leaf summaries.

`load_prompts(fs, dir)` reads `summarizer-leaf.md` and `summarizer-rollup.md` from `prompts_dir` once per run; both must exist. `summarize_leaf(fs, agent, prompts, src, model, progress)` validates the source path (rejects unsafe paths and gated targets via `ctx_core::access`), reads the file, sends `SOURCE_PATH: {src}\n\n{contents}` with the leaf prompt to the agent, and writes the output to the `.ctx` path. `summarize_rollup(fs, agent, prompts, dir, model, progress)` assembles rollup input via `crate::rollup_input` (which constructs the directory's context from child `.ctx` files), sends it with the rollup prompt to the agent, and writes to the rollup path.

`run()` and `run_with_prompts()` are the entry points; the latter decouples prompt source from the target tree root. `affected_dirs(targets)` computes all ancestor directories of targets in leaf-up order (depth descending, then lexicographic), ensuring rollups build from children up. `scope_check(count, approve)` gates runs with more than `MAX_TARGETS` (50) targets unless explicitly approved—a safety valve against accidental whole-repo cost.